item.description:
@Bebemycat2 wrote:

My way of doing it:

Note* I added “Activateclient” this will simply make sure the targeted client is on top before the main scriot starts.

[code]///// Autologin\\
////First Script\\
/// By Blizzind \\\

Program Autologin;

const
Username=‘Blizmine 2’;
password=‘mining’;

procedure Login;
MoveMouseSmooth(462,292);
ClickMouse(462,292,True);
Wait(1250);
MoveMouseSmooth(377,256);
ClickMouse(377,256,True);
Wait(1250);
SendKeys(Username);
Wait(2500);
MoveMouseSmooth(378,272);
ClickMouse(378,272,True);
Wait(1250);
SendKeys(Password);
Wait(2500);
MoveMouseSmooth(305,322);
ClickMouse(305,322,True);
Wait(2500);
end;

begin
activateclient;
Login;
end.[/code]

item.title: [Error] (31:1): Unexpected end of file
item.dc:creator: @Arkanor Arkanor
item.description:
@Arkanor wrote:

Remove the Procedure Login;

The reason that you don’t need that is that you’re creating a procedure when in fact you don’t have a main loop. So, by removing the designating line for a procedure, you create a main loop.
